rate-mortgage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efixed-rate%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20your%20interest%20rate%20remains%20the%20same%20for%20the%20entire%20time%20you%20have%20the%20loan.%20This%20keeps%20your%20monthly%20payment%20the%20same%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20name%20suggests%2C%20adjustable-rate%20mortgages%20work%20differently.%20You'll%20start%20off%20with%20the%20same%20rate%20for%20a%20few%20years%2C%20but%20after%20that%2C%20your%20rate%20can%20change%20periodically.%20This%20means%20that%20if%20average%20rates%20have%20gone%20up%2C%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Faverage-mortgage-payment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emortgage%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20increase.%20If%20they've%20gone%20down%2C%20your%20payment%20will%20decrease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227eff4530-7cf2-4894-aa6c-b40a38bebea6%5C%22%3E5%2F1%20adjustable-rate%20mortgage%20example%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20popular%20type%20of%20ARM%20is%20the%205%2F1%20ARM.%20We'll%20use%20it%20as%20an%20example%20to%20show%20how%20these%20types%20of%20mortgages%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20number%20tells%20you%20how%20long%20you'll%20keep%20the%20rate%20you%20were%20initially%20given.%20So%2C%20say%20you%20get%20a%205%2F1%20ARM%20with%20a%206.20%25%20interest%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20five%20years%20you%20have%20the%20mortgage%2C%20your%20rate%20will%20stay%20at%206.20%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20number%20tells%20you%20how%20often%20the%20rate%20will%20adjust%20after%20the%20initial%20fixed-rate%20period%20is%20over.%20With%20a%205%2F1%20ARM%2C%20the%20rate%20adjusts%20once%20a%20year.%20If%20over%20those%20first%20five%20years%20market%20conditions%20cause%20interest%20rates%20to%20rise%2C%20you'll%20likely%20end%20up%20with%20a%20higher%20rate%20when%20it%20comes%20time%20to%20adjust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive-year%20ARMs%20also%20come%20in%20a%205%2F6%20variation%2